originalText.text: We took a Jewish food and history tour of the Lower East Side with Myra. She was an excellent guide — warm, energetic, and knowledgeable. She shared great anecdotes with us, and gave us the flavor of the neighborhood,, as well as the facts. My husband, sisters, brother in law and I all loved the tour, and had a lovely afternoon with Myra. Highly recommended.

originalText.text: I took the Nosh Walking Tour for Ethnic Foods in Rego Park Queens.  I think we paid too much money for what we experienced.  Myra seems like a nice enough person, however, we did not get exactly what was advertised.  We were supposed to have a sit-down meal in a restaurant.  When we got to the restaurant, we were told we needed a reservation.  She should have researched this/known this beforehand. We got take out and proceeded to walk to a schoolyard where she said we could eat.  The schoolyard was locked.  We had to walk a few more blocks and eat the foods on a park bench.  Most of the samplings from the bakeries and supermarkets were sweets.  In addition, one of the items--samsa--we had to eat on top of a closed garbage disposal.  As I said, the tour-guide seemed friendly, but this tour was not well organized and was way too much money for what we experienced.  I would also have liked more cultural, culinary information.

originalText.text: The presenter has no idea of food safety or hygiene. She licked her fingers and handed out food. It was so disgusting and I would never attend another. I would have liked to order for myself so I would get food that I like. I also wish there was more historical info incorporated.
